# Docker Standards

## Dockerfile — multi-stage, non-root, pinned, minimal

```dockerfile
# WRONG — single stage, root user, latest tag, unoptimised
FROM golang:latest
COPY . .
RUN go build -o app .
CMD ["./app"]

# RIGHT — multi-stage, pinned digest, non-root, minimal final image
# ── Build stage ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
FROM golang:1.22-alpine3.19 AS builder
WORKDIR /src

# Download dependencies first (cached layer unless go.mod changes)
COPY go.mod go.sum ./
RUN go mod download -x

# Build with reproducible settings
COPY . .
RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 \
    go build \
    -ldflags="-s -w -X main.Version=${VERSION}" \
    -trimpath \
    -o /app/proxy \
    ./services/proxy/cmd/proxy

# ── Final stage ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
FROM gcr.io/distroless/static-debian12:nonroot AS runtime
# distroless/static: no shell, no package manager, attack surface ~5MB

COPY --from=builder --chown=nonroot:nonroot /app/proxy /proxy

EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["/proxy"]
```

## Never use `latest` tag — always pin to an immutable digest or exact version

```yaml
# WRONG
image: postgres:latest
image: redis:latest

# RIGHT — pinned exact version (update deliberately, not accidentally)
image: postgres:16.2-alpine3.19
image: redis:7.2-alpine3.19
```

## Docker Compose — health checks, resource limits, no hardcoded secrets

```yaml
# WRONG
services:
  postgres:
    image: postgres:latest
    environment:
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: password123
    # no health check
    # no resource limits

# RIGHT
services:
  postgres:
    image: postgres:16.2-alpine3.19
    environment:
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD:?POSTGRES_PASSWORD is required}
      POSTGRES_DB:       ${POSTGRES_DB:-ibex_dev}
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "pg_isready -U postgres"]
      interval: 5s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 10
      start_period: 10s
    deploy:
      resources:
        limits:
          cpus: "2"
          memory: 1G
    networks:
      - ibex_internal
    volumes:
      - postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data

networks:
  ibex_internal:
    driver: bridge

volumes:
  postgres_data:
    driver: local
```

## .dockerignore — always present

```text
# .dockerignore
.git
.github
.cursor
docs/
*.md
*_test.go
**/*_test.go
infra/
dist/
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
```

## Never put secrets in Dockerfiles or docker-compose.yml

Secrets come from environment variables, mounted files, or secret management systems (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager). The repo must never contain credentials.

```yaml
# WRONG — secret in compose file
environment:
  JWT_SECRET: "my-super-secret-key-123"

# RIGHT — reference to env var, which is populated from secret manager
environment:
  JWT_SECRET: ${JWT_SECRET:?JWT_SECRET is required}
```
